# 2p_ctf_pickup — host (RED) walks into the BLUE flag and verifies
# pickup fires server-side, broadcasts to client. Pairs with
# 2p_ctf_pickup.client.shot — that test walks the client (BLUE) into
# the RED flag from the opposite side.
#
# Setup: peer_spawn places both mechs right on the OPPOSING team's
# flag platform (Crossfire flag platforms are at the far left/right
# of the map). Each player walks INTO their target flag and pickup
# should fire on the authoritative server.
#
# Crossfire flag y: 1520. Flag-platform top: 1536. Mech standing
# pelvis at platform_top - 36 = 1500, chest at pelvis - 32 = 1468.
# Vertical chest-to-flag distance: 52 px (currently > FLAG_TOUCH_RADIUS_PX
# = 36 — REGRESSION if pickup never fires).
#
# RED flag at (480, 1520). BLUE flag at (4000, 1520).

window 1280 720
out build/shots/net/host_ctf_pickup
network host 24034
name HostRed

# Park the host right next to BLUE flag (4000, 1520). x=3950 places
# pelvis 50 px west of the flag staff so we walk RIGHT into it.
spawn_at 3950 1496
peer_spawn 1 530 1496

contact_sheet sheet cols 4 cell 320 180

at 140 shot t140_round_start
at 200 shot t200_settled_near_blue_flag

# Walk right into the flag. RUN_SPEED ~4.6 px/tick — 50 px = 11 ticks.
at 220 press right
at 280 release right
at 250 shot t250_walking_into_flag
at 290 shot t290_pickup_window
at 360 shot t360_post_pickup

at 660 end
